    "encrypted": "false",
    "long_instructions": "## Do This:\r\n\r\nYou're coding a tool that generates a music playlist for a friend. The function is supposed to print a message that says it's creating a playlist for the person whose name you pass in. But right now, the code crashes as soon as you run it! \r\n\r\n1. Look at the function `make_playlist(user)`. It's supposed to print a message that uses the person's name.\r\n\r\n2. Try running the code. Read the error message carefully.\r\n\r\n3. Figure out what's wrong and fix the function so it prints the message correctly.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n<i class=\"fa-solid fa-laptop\"></i> **Coding Tip**\r\n\r\nYou can only use a parameter inside the function where it’s defined. And you must use the exact name of the parameter — spelling matters!",
